==Dutch==
===Noun===
'''knoop''' {{m}} (Plural: [[knopen]], diminutive: [[knoopje]])

#A [[loop]] of string or any other long flexible material which cannot be untied without pulling part of the string through the loops.
#:''ik zit in de knoop'': I'm in a hard spot. I'm all tied up.
#A unit of [[velocity]], corresponding to traveling a distance of 1 [[nautical mile]] per [[hour]].

